.TH "t4_fw_hello" 9 "t4_fw_hello" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4_fw_hello \- establish communication with FW
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4_fw_hello
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mbox "  ","
.BI "unsigned int evt_mbox "  ","
.BI "enum dev_master master "  ","
.BI "enum dev_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "mbox" 12
mailbox to use for the FW command
.IP "evt_mbox" 12
mailbox to receive async FW events
.IP "master" 12
specifies the caller's willingness to be the device master
.IP "state" 12
returns the current device state (if non-NULL)

Issues a command to establish communication with FW.  Returns either
an error (negative integer) or the mailbox of the Master PF.
